---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Resources — As-Built Company">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow">Resources</div>
      <h1>Knowledge. Tools. <span class="accent">Better Projects.</span></h1>
      <p class="lead">Field-tested guides on 3D laser scanning, as-built drawings, and how to spec the work so you get back what you actually need.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Featured Resources</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-4">
        <a href="/resources/ultimate-guide-as-built-drawings/" class="card" style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit;">
          <div class="card-image"><span class="card-badge">Guide</span>The Ultimate Guide<br />to As-Built Drawings</div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>The Ultimate Guide to As-Built Drawings</h3>
            <p>What as-builts are, what should be in a real set, who needs them, and how to specify accuracy correctly using USIBD LOA.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <span>9 min read</span>
            <span class="arrow-link">→</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/resources/2d-vs-3d-as-built-drawings/" class="card" style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit;">
          <div class="card-image"><span class="card-badge">Article</span>2D vs 3D As-Built<br />Drawings</div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>2D vs 3D As-Built Drawings: Which Do You Need?</h3>
            <p>When 2D plans make sense, when a Revit model is worth the cost, and how to avoid over-ordering deliverables you won&rsquo;t use.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <span>6 min read</span>
            <span class="arrow-link">→</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/resources/point-cloud-vs-manual-measurement/" class="card" style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit;">
          <div class="card-image"><span class="card-badge">Case Study</span>Point Cloud Scanning<br />vs Manual Measurement</div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>How I Measure Buildings With Point Cloud Scanning</h3>
            <p>The honest side-by-side: tape measure vs Leica BLK2GO. Time, money, labor, accuracy &mdash; what really changes when you scan instead of measure by hand.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <span>8 min read</span>
            <span class="arrow-link">→</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/resources/as-built-request-checklist/" class="card" style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit;">
          <div class="card-image"><span class="card-badge">Template</span>As-Built Drawing<br />Request Checklist</div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3>As-Built Drawing Request Checklist</h3>
            <p>A scope-tight checklist for clients requesting as-builts. What to send so quotes are accurate, comparable, and not wildly off.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <span>5 min read</span>
            <span class="arrow-link">→</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-surface">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-strip">
        <div class="text">
          <h3>Have a project to scope?</h3>
          <p>The articles cover the theory. We&rsquo;ll give you a quote within one business day.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn">Get a Quote <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
